2) Rotate by π/4: multiply by e^{iπ/4} = (1+i)/√2.
(z - c) e^{iπ/4} = [√2 (1 - 3i)] * [(1+i)/√2] = (1 - 3i)(1 + i) = 4 - 2i.

3) Add center: w = c + (4 - 2i) = (2 - 3i) + (4 - 2i) = 6 - 5i.

4) Self-check: |z - c| = |4 - 2i| = √20 = 2√5, same as |w - c|, so rotation is consistent.

